cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SD

The paper proposes neural network based mixture models for generating samples and classification. This falls under the domain of machine learning and specifically, deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of neural networks for generating samples, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves the use of expectation-maximization based algorithms for learning parameters, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE) and statistics (cs.SD). Therefore, the likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, and cs.SD, in decreasing order of likelihood.
